      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why does DayShift pair caffeine with L-theanine?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Caffeine on its own can produce jitters and a crash. L-theanine is an amino acid studied for promoting calm, focused brain states. Paired at a 2:1 ratio (L-theanine to caffeine), the combination has been studied for faster reaction times, better attention, and fewer of the over-stimulation effects of caffeine alone. DayShift uses 240 mg of L-theanine and 120 mg of caffeine, exactly the studied ratio."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Does DayShift cause a caffeine crash?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "DayShift is formulated specifically to reduce the crash associated with caffeine alone. The 2:1 L-theanine to caffeine pairing has been studied for smoother focus and energy, and DayShift also includes adaptogens and amino acids that support sustained mental performance beyond caffeine's window."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is DayShift caffeine natural or synthetic?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "DayShift uses natural caffeine from green tea leaf extract. Most energy drinks and pre-workouts use synthetic caffeine, the cheapest form."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can I drink coffee with DayShift?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "DayShift is designed to give you a complete daily dose of caffeine paired with L-theanine and other nootropics. If you usually drink multiple cups of coffee, consider whether replacing one or more with DayShift makes sense for your total caffeine intake. As with any caffeinated product, monitor your individual tolerance."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

